The Judicial Service Commission (JSC) has shortlisted 10 people, among them five judges, for the position of Chief Justice to replace Mr David Maraga who retired in January. 

In an announcement, the JSC dropped three applicants from the list of 13 people who had applied for the position at the deadline on February 9. 



